pet.name: Echo in FL
pet.description:
Hello, hello, hello…my name is “Echo”, I’m 3 years old. My brother, “Draco”, and I came to Dogue de Bordeaux Rescue or DDBR of no fault of our own. I am very attached to my brother and we would love to be adopted together. I am a very sweet and shy gal. I like to do everything my brother does. It makes me sad when he goes somewhere without me. I love attention and for someone to scratch my belly. I also love going for walks early in the day or later in the afternoon/evening when it’s not terribly hot outside, I walk very well on a leash and never pull. I am gentle with taking food from your hand and will not take food unless it is offered to me. I like to chew on bones but I have never learned to play with toys. I would like it if you could teach me! I am a fast learner and aim to please my owner. I also love long naps and car rides. I am a full time inside dogue only as us dogues don’t do particularly well in the heat for long periods of time – I do love to romp around outside with my brother but only for short supervised durations. The vet says I am in good health however I do have a broken tail from an accident when I was a puppy – the vet states it does not hurt me however I prefer it not be touched. I have been spayed and am up to date on my shots. I have a microchip and take my Trifexis every month year round like a good girl. I came from a family with (2) small children so my brother and I are likely good with children and, unlike my brother, I’m also well-mannered around other dogs. My brother and I have been living in boarding facilities (a cage) in Central FL since April 4th and are very much in need of a foster home until able to be adopted. DDBR states they may have the ability to arrange transport outside of the state. If you have been on the fence about fostering, now is the time to just do it! DDBR has been trying to find help for us for a while and is dedicated to saving me and my brother but they cannot do this without some assistance.
Completed application and reference/home check required. Standard adoption fee is $450 applies to all of our rescues. We do NOT ship or fly rescues as it’s too stressful on them.
If you are interested in any of our rescues, please complete our adoption application, it can be completed on line. Further information and questions, please contact Laurie at roscoberner@gmail.com
Donations are always needed to help with rescue dog expenses. Your tax deductible donations are greatly needed and appreciated. Paypal to donations@ddbrescue.org or check to: DDB Rescue, PO BOX 1245, Sutherlin, OR 97479

pet.name: Miss LuLu has one Blue Eye and one Brown
pet.description:
Adoption events are every Saturday in March at the Pet Supermarket 2449 S. Hiawassee Rd. Orlando 32835
LuLu was found by the State Troopers in Tn. She was seen running back and forth on the highway by people going to work. LuLu would often sit by the median watching the cars go by. Lots of people called in about her. You see there was snow on the ground and it was cold in the Tn Mountains. When the Troopers went out to get her, she ran and they followed. She led them right to her den with her litter of sweet babies. She showed them where she had hidden them and kept them safe. Lulu was happy to be rescued with her puppies by the kind deputies. In no time at all, they were bathed and snuggled in a warm bed at the Dr. Hood Memorial Shelter. Well ... that was some time ago. The babies have all been adopted and Mom is just waiting for you to take her home. LuLu is a little bit picky. She loves people but would do best in a home where she is the one and only. If you have room in your heart and home for this big beautiful girl, Please call us. We would love to meet you., and LuLu is waiting just for you.

pet.name: Yoyo (LR) 2.1.10
pet.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.FIV +Yoyo is a quiet, calm and collected boy. Yoyo is FIV+, which just means if his white blood cells decrease, his ability to fight infection decreases. The virus is slow acting and most cats live a normal, healthy life span. (The virus cannot be passed to humans or other species.) Yoyo is not aggressive and can live with FIV negative cats. He was extremely shy when he was trapped. He is as sweet as can be now and his meow is so soft and low that it will melt your heart. He was taken to to the vet with a UTI blockage when he was first rescued and he has to be on Hills prescription diet all his life. He does walk a bit funny, his tail is always down and his hip seems to be to one side. Maybe he suffered some trauma when living outside. This doesn't stop him, he is fine and gets around and plays with no problem.

pet.name: Zorrita (LR) 6.1.08
pet.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website. Est. birthday 6/01/2008
Zorrita, which means "little fox" was trapped in 2009 with her kitten which was added to another litter. She used to be very feral and she could not be approached. Her kitten was socialized fully vetted and found a furever home. Zorrita was then also spayed and vetted and stayed outside and was taken care of. She did well with the other kitties so her rescuer decided to bring her inside. She has lived with her foster family for about 9 yrs. Over time with love and care from her foster family she will let you cautiously pet her and will even let you rub her tummy. As soon as you do she will slowly start to purr!!! She is very food motivated and will loudly meow when it's time for her food. Zorrita looks like a mini Maine
Coon
mix and loves to have her long hair brushed. She is fearful of strangers at first so it's best she is socialized in a space where she cannot hide in or under something. We know that with time and patience this beautiful girl will come around. She actually does fine with other kitties that are calm and cat friendly but at this point would most likely be best as an only kitty. She just needs that special someone who can give her plenty of time to get acclimated and understand that she needs and wants love but just has to earn your trust. She deserves to live out her senior years in a warm and cozy furever home where she can receive all the love she so deserves.
